# 3. 力になりたい

Shiho: Oh, about what aspirations you hold for your music...?
Miku: In that case, I'd like to hear your answer, Honami.
Honami: Okay.
Honami: So, I realized that...
Honami: I want to be able to support everyone in Leo/need.
Shiho: Support us...?
Honami: Yes. Ichika said how I should think about the things that I like and such when it came to that question.
Ichika: Oh...
Honami: And seeing Saki just now, I had a thought. Helping others makes me incredibly happy...
Ichika: Helping others...
Ichika: Right... You've basically been doing that forever.
Saki: Yeah, you're always willing to lend others your ear when you see that something's bothering them...
Shiho: Which has saved us more than a few times.
Honami: Th-Thank you...
Honami: Also, um... My desire to help others also extends to our band.
Honami: Each of you has your own hopes and aspirations, so I want to do everything in my power to make those a reality.
Ichika: Honami...
Honami: I remember feeling so happy when I saw how much the audience enjoyed our solo show. But that was only part of the reason...
Honami: I was also happy because I was able to assist in getting your thoughts and feelings across to them.
Saki: Hona...
Honami: I think it's on the same level of wanting to play music that moves people's hearts... No, it may mean more to me than that.
Honami: I want to help make all your aspirations a reality... I think that's what matters most to me.
Ichika: I see...
Ichika: That's what you want to do through your music...
Honami: Yes...
Honami: But I'm still not sure if it's okay for me to say that...
Shiho: What?
Honami: I mean, my answer... It's so different from your goals. You all want to do what you can for the audience...
Shiho: Yeah, you're right in that sense, but...
MEIKO: I see nothing wrong with what you said.
MEIKO: You arrived on that after spending a lot of time thinking about it, so it must be the right answer.
Honami: Huh?
Rin: Yeah, I agree! Also, I really love how you want to help everyone!
KAITO: I also think it suits you well...
Honami: Oh...
Honami: Thank you all very much...
Miku: I guess that means you're all set to go now.
Ichika: Yeah, through our music, we're aspiring to...
Honami: Move people's hearts, cheer them up and bring them together...
Saki: With a certain someone helping us make all those things a reality!
Shiho: In summary, we're all over the place...
Saki: But the next step is to figure out what Leo/need's gonna aspire to, right? That sounds even harder! What should we do?
Ichika: Yeah, you might be right... Mr. Shindo said we'll figure that out after we've solidified our individual goals...
Ichika: But how do we turn those into the one thing Leo/need is going to aspire to?
Honami: We can't just choose one since they're all so different, and they mean everything to each of us...
Miku: Are they that different...? I actually believe otherwise.
Honami: You do?
Miku: Think about Shiho's... She wants your music to move people's hearts...
Miku: Saki, you want to cheer people up. And Ichika, you want to bring people together. Don't those both come from the same place?
Shiho: I mean...
Honami: Oh, wait a second. That means mine is somewhat different...
Honami: Because my goal doesn't really stem from wanting to move people's hearts.
Luka: Oh, are you sure?
Honami: Huh?
Luka: Because you supporting Leo/need means helping to produce music that moves people's hearts, no?
Luka: Which is why I think it has a fairly firm connection to what the others are aspiring to, Honami.
Honami: Oh...
Miku: Then, isn't that what's tying you all together?
Ichika: We all want to move people's hearts through our music...
Ichika: Yeah, I think Miku's right...
Saki: Wait, is that okay? That was like our very first answer.
Miku: What's wrong with that? I say nothing if it's what Leo/need's really about.
Luka: I agree. It all stems from that in the end.
Luka: Dissecting that is what allowed you all to come up with your individual goals and aspirations.
Shiho: Right... Mr. Shindo even said that it's okay for us to go with something we've already thought of.
Honami: Okay, then... Let's make that our collective goal.
Saki: Yeah! Alright, that settles that...!
Saki: Now, all we gotta do is tell Mr. Shindo what we're gonna aspire to as a band...!
